    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "t_start": 10.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "narration_text": "To catch the error, you measure parity. An ancilla qubit applies CNOT to qubit one, then CNOT to qubit two. It reads out whether the pair has flipped. One ancilla, two data qubits, two gates.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "new_visual_element": "[CIRCUIT] ancilla with CNOT to Q1 then CNOT to Q2",
      "audio_file": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 13.19,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-fault-tolerance/clips/B02.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B02.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "t_start": 22.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "narration_text": "Now the ancilla itself has an error at gate one. A single gate fails. The code was designed to handle single errors. This should be fine. But it is not.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "new_visual_element": "[CIRCUIT] same circuit with X error on ancilla at gate 1",
      "audio_file": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.16,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-fault-tolerance/clips/B03.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B03.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "t_start": 34.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "A single ancilla gate fails. The 3-qubit code is designed to correct any single-qubit error. Why does one gate failure break a code that should handle one error?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "SlateCard",
          "provenance": "proven-core/SlateCard",
          "version": "1",
          "props": {
            "headline": "A single ancilla gate fails. The 3-qubit code is designed to\u2026",
            "eyebrow": "",
