    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "t_start": 49.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 14.0,
      "narration_text": "After the first CNOT, the ancilla is in an error state. But it has not finished its job. Gate two \u2014 CNOT from corrupted ancilla to qubit two \u2014 now copies the ancilla's error onto qubit two. One ancilla error becomes two data-qubit errors.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "new_visual_element": "[CIRCUIT] error on ancilla propagating through gate 2 to Q2",
      "audio_file": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 15.7,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-fault-tolerance/clips/B06.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B06.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "t_start": 63.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "narration_text": "The three-qubit code corrects errors on one qubit at a time. When it sees two data qubits flipped, it applies the wrong correction. The logical qubit is not saved \u2014 it fails. One physical gate error causes a logical qubit failure.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "new_visual_element": "[TABLE] 2-qubit error vs. code correction table: wrong outcome",
      "audio_file": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 15.54,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-fault-tolerance/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "t_start": 75.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 5.0,
      "narration_text": "The distinction: error correction versus fault tolerance.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "SlateCard",
          "provenance": "proven-core/SlateCard",
