    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "t_start": 80.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 13.0,
      "narration_text": "Error correction handles errors on data qubits. Fault tolerance is a separate requirement: a single error anywhere in the syndrome circuit \u2014 on any gate, any ancilla \u2014 must propagate to at most one data-qubit error. Fault tolerance requires the syndrome circuit to be redesigned.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "new_visual_element": "[COMPARE] error correction vs fault tolerance side-by-side",
      "audio_file": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 17.79,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-fault-tolerance/clips/B09.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B09.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "t_start": 93.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 5.0,
      "narration_text": "The fix: separate ancillas.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "SlateCard",
          "provenance": "proven-core/SlateCard",
          "version": "1",
          "props": {
            "headline": "The fix: separate ancillas.",
            "eyebrow": "",
            "topic": ""
          },
          "rendered": {
            "out": "media/B10.mp4",
            "at": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "card": {
        "kind": "section",
        "copy": "THE FAULT-TOLERANT FIX"
      },
      "new_visual_element": "[SECTION] fix",
      "audio_file": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 1.8,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-fault-tolerance/clips/B10.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-fault-tolerance/mp3/beat-B10.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "t_start": 98.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 14.0,
      "narration_text": "Use one ancilla per stabilizer instead of one ancilla for both. Each ancilla touches only one data qubit. Now a single ancilla error can corrupt only one data qubit. The code corrects one error \u2014 and now it always has at most one to correct.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
